  <body>
    <p>This section explains the behaviour of the <uicontrol>Track Changes</uicontrol> feature
      depending on the context and whether it is activated.</p>
    <p>You can use the <uicontrol>Track Changes</uicontrol> feature to keep track of multiple
      actions.</p>
    <p>Possible change tracking scenarios:<ul>
        <li><xref href="keep-tracking-inserted-content.dita#keep-tracking-inserted-content">Keep
            tracking of inserted content</xref></li>
        <li><xref href="keep-tracking-surround.dita#keep-tracking-surround">Keep tracking of
            surrounded content</xref></li>
        <li><xref href="keep-tracking-deleted-characters.dita#keep-tracking-deleted-characters">Keep
            tracking of deleted characters</xref></li>
        <li><xref href="keep-tracking-deleted-content.dita#keep-tracking-deleted-content">Keep
            tracking of deleted content</xref></li>
        <li><xref href="keep-tracking-copied-content.dita#keep-tracking-copied-content">Keep
            tracking of copied content</xref></li>
        <li><xref href="keep-tracking-pasted-content.dita#keep-tracking-pasted-content">Keep
            tracking of pasted content</xref></li>
        <li><xref href="keep-tracking-attribute-changes.dita#keep-tracking-attribute-changes">Keep
            tracking of attribute changes</xref></li>
      </ul></p>
  </body>
